    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for a Medium model risk, Medium model influence, Medium decision consequence context of use. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) reflects a single ASTM F1717 test condition and is accepted because the standard condition is the regulatory reference condition and the shortfall does not materially affect confidence in the three primary QoIs, all of which satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the Accepted decision.",
